data.description: Beautiful home in Bexley. Don't miss the chance to own your best life in a place where new homes lead to stronger connections, fun, nature, and new friendships. There are spaces for all ages to play – with seven parks and miles of stunning trails that lead to  fit stations, dog parks, playgrounds, full-service café and The Bexley Club.  Bexley is an amazing community in the Tampa Bay area. When you call Bexley home, you are just a few steps from miles of trails, parks, green spaces, and conservation areas. This Florida master-planned community, situated just north of Tampa, has amenities fit for everyone. Bexley features easy access to downtown Tampa, airports, beaches, healthcare, entertainment, and so much more. Bexley residents are zoned to attend the highly rated Bexley Elementary School, which is a public school located within the community that enrolls kindergarteners to fifth graders.Known as the home of the Ravens, Charles S. Rushe Middle School has been part of the Land O’ Lakes community for over 12 years and is another top-notch, Bexley-zoned school option. For the last 7 years, it has been designated as an “A” School by the Florida Department of Education.  Among those standout qualities, Charles S. Rushe is also the only middle school in the Pasco County region to offer a self-contained gifted program.Bexley residents are able to attend Sunlake High School, which serves around 2,000 students ranging from grades 9 – 12. The high school offers an array of classes, including a full slate of Advanced Placement classes.
